# Adversary fixture: FM3 — <triple> element with wrong arity (4 children)
# Hypothesis: the TriX spec §3 requires exactly 3 RDF-term children per
#   <triple> element. This document supplies 4 children, which violates the
#   schema. A conformant parser must reject the document. A lenient parser
#   may silently discard the extra child or accept the first 3 terms,
#   producing an AcceptRejectSplit divergence.
# Expected outcome: reject
outcome: reject
fact-count: 0
divergence-hypothesis: AcceptRejectSplit — a parser that takes only the first
  three children and ignores extra ones will accept the document and produce
  1 fact; a conformant parser rejects it as malformed.
spec-ref: TriX spec §3 (HPL-2004-56) — "A triple element has exactly three
  children, representing the subject, predicate, and object of the triple."
